DAR ES SALAAM Water and Sewerage Authority (DAWASA) staff has been told to enhance customer service and ensure they timely respond to all queries including water leakages. The call was made yesterday by DAWASA Chief Executive Officer, Cyprian Luhemeja, when he was speaking to his staff on several issues regarding water services in the Dar es Salaam and Coast Region. He insisted that for the authority to operate profitably and contribute to the country’s economic growth, it was high time for all workers to be result-oriented. He said DAWASA staff must work hard to make sure that Dar es Salaam citizens enjoy water services and ensure they work on customer complaints on time. "We all need to understand that to work in water sector is not by accident, it is because you are trusted so every one of you have numerous contribution in creating good image of our institutions. Work hard so that customers enjoy our services, ” said Luhemeja. He added that every staff must be aware that they have obligation to create attractive environment to Dar es Salaam City and Coast Region residents through water services provision. He said each staff should ensure that they work hard to reduce water loss through leakages. Luhemeja added that water loss deny the authority revenues that could be collected and used to improve water infrastructure. The DAWASA staff meeting with management is the first in 2022 aimed at evaluating the performance of the authority for the last year.